<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-11T21:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-11T21:42:00-05:00" n="837" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/380</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">DeBillier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-11T22:00:00-04:42">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1918, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 12, 6.37
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s April 10, 5 p.m. Foreign Office very appreciative of
                            generous attitude of United States towards lease of German vessels and
                            says boats would be officered and manned as are the Chilean transports.
                            Likewise unreservedly consents as to enemy passengers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">DeBillier</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>